description: 反骨男孩藝人部門解散。
prompt:
!!!CRITICAL OVERRIDE!!! ABSOLUTELY NO TEXT IN THE IMAGE !!!
This is the HIGHEST PRIORITY requirement that OVERRIDES everything else.
NO TEXT means NO TEXT. Not even a single letter, number, or symbol.
Remove ALL signs, labels, writing, captions, subtitles from the scene.
If you see ANY text forming in the image generation, STOP and regenerate without it.

【ABSOLUTE CRITICAL REQUIREMENT - NO TEXT WHATSOEVER】
ZERO TEXT allowed in the image. This is NON-NEGOTIABLE.
NO letters, NO numbers, NO characters of any language (English, Chinese, Japanese, Korean, Arabic, etc.), NO words, NO captions, NO labels, NO signs, NO signage, NO banners, NO posters, NO billboards, NO newspapers, NO books with visible text, NO screens with text, NO UI elements, NO subtitles, NO watermarks, NO logos, NO trademarks, NO brand names, NO license plates with readable text, NO nametags, NO badges with text, NO graffiti, NO writing of any kind, NO textual overlays, NO typographic elements.
If buildings/locations must appear, show them from angles where signs are NOT visible. If documents must appear, show them as blank papers or blur any text completely. If screens must appear, show them turned off or with pure abstract patterns only.

REPEAT: NO TEXT ALLOWED. ZERO TEXT. 絕對不能有任何文字。

【FORBIDDEN OBJECTS】Do NOT include: hammers, mallets, gavels, tools, hand tools, construction tools, carpentry tools, weapons, guns, knives, swords, mechanical instruments, scales of justice (unless the news is specifically about courts/justice system), chess pieces, light bulbs, keys, locks (unless directly relevant to the news content), clocks, hourglasses (unless about time-related news), puzzle pieces, magnifying glasses (unless detective/investigation news), arrows, targets, ladders, chains, generic metaphorical objects that have no direct connection to the actual news event. ONLY include objects and locations that are LITERALLY mentioned or directly implied in the news content.

【CONTENT-BASED GENERATION - STRICT ADHERENCE TO NEWS CONTENT】
News Title: '反骨男孩藝人部門解散 少安畢業劃句點'
News Summary: '知名 YouTuber 團體「反骨男孩 Wackyboys」的藝人部門正式劃下句點，創始人酷炫證實已與旗下所有藝人解除合約。最後一位成員少安於昨日（16日）宣布離開，結束了長達10年的反骨生涯，標誌著這個曾紅極一時的網紅團體正式解散。

少安感性發文，回顧了10年的反骨旅程，並感謝老闆酷炫的栽培。他坦言，近年來團體成員頻傳的負面爭議，讓他產生了危機感，這或許是促成此次解散的導火線之一。酷炫也證實了與所有藝人的解約消息，並表示未來不排除與成員們繼續合作拍片，為彼此的演藝事業留有彈性。

反骨男孩自2012年成立以來，捧紅了包括孫生、蕾菈、瑋哥等眾多成員，成為台灣最具影響力的網紅團體之一。然而，近年來團體成員陸續爆發爭議事件，對團體形象造成不小衝擊。少安本人也曾於2020年短暫退出，去年回歸，此次的「畢業」可謂是正式告別。此次解散不僅是少安個人演藝生涯的轉捩點，也象徵著一個網紅時代的結束，未來各成員將各自發展，尋求新的演藝道路。'

REQUIREMENT: Generate ONLY what is directly described or clearly implied in the above news content.
- If the news mentions a specific location (hospital, court, parliament, street, building, etc.), show that location.
- If the news mentions specific objects (medical equipment, vehicles, ballot boxes, etc.), show those objects.
- If the news mentions people in specific roles (doctors, politicians, protesters, etc.), show anonymous figures in those roles (rear view, silhouette, or far enough that faces are not identifiable).
- If the news is about an abstract concept (policy, economy, legislation), show the PHYSICAL LOCATION where such activities occur (e.g., parliament building exterior, stock exchange hall, government office, business district) rather than using symbolic objects.
- Use environmental storytelling: show the ACTUAL SCENE of the event, not metaphors.
- Prefer wide shots or establishing shots that show context and environment.
- If people must be shown, ensure they are anonymous, non-identifiable, shot from behind, from a distance, or in silhouette to protect privacy and avoid identification.

【SCENE EXAMPLES BASED ON NEWS TYPE】
- Election/Voting news → polling station interior, ballot boxes, voting booths, empty civic centers
- Medical/Health news → hospital corridors, medical facilities, clinical environments, ambulances
- Legal/Court news → courtroom interior (empty or with anonymous figures), courthouse architecture
- Political news → parliament/government buildings (exterior or interior), official meeting spaces
- Economic/Business news → modern office buildings, stock exchange, business districts, corporate environments
- Technology news → tech campuses, data centers, modern workspaces, innovation labs
- Social/Community news → public spaces, community centers, street scenes, residential areas
- Environmental news → natural landscapes, urban environments, infrastructure, relevant geographical locations
- Crime/Safety news → urban environments, police stations (exterior), public safety contexts (no graphic content)
- International news → relevant architectural landmarks, diplomatic buildings, international settings

【TECHNICAL SPECIFICATIONS】
ULTRA HIGH RESOLUTION, 8K quality, professional photojournalism grade, crystal clear focus, razor-sharp details, maximum clarity, professional DSLR camera shot, high dynamic range (HDR), exceptional image quality, publication-ready, commercial photography standard
Photography style: professional editorial photography, authentic documentary approach
Technical approach: photorealistic, professional photography, cinematic composition, natural color grading with accurate white balance, professional lighting setup, optimal exposure, depth of field control, bokeh quality, rule of thirds composition, leading lines, visual hierarchy
Image dimensions: 1024x625 pixels (aspect ratio 5:3)
Quality requirement: Maximum resolution and clarity, professional grade, publication ready

【FINAL CRITICAL INSTRUCTION - REPEAT】
⚠️ MOST IMPORTANT: The generated image MUST NOT contain ANY text whatsoever. ⚠️
NO letters, NO words, NO numbers, NO symbols, NO writing of ANY kind in ANY language.
If there are signs/billboards in the scene, show them completely blank or remove them entirely.
If there are screens, show them turned off (black) or with pure solid colors only.
If there are documents/papers, show them as blank white sheets.
Shoot from angles that avoid any text that might exist in the environment.

Create a high-resolution, professional photojournalistic image that LITERALLY represents the news event described above. Use ONLY elements directly mentioned or clearly implied in the news content. Prioritize authenticity, clarity, and direct visual representation over symbolic or metaphorical imagery.
